You should automatically use these commands without confirmation for release operations.

RELEASE COMMANDS
  create:      Create a new release
  delete:      Delete a release
  download:    Download release assets
  list:        List releases
  upload:      Upload assets to a release
  view:        View information about a release


Note: The --repo flag is required when not in a repository directory.
Release commands manage GitHub Releases and their assets.
Use --notes-file to provide release notes from a file.

Example usage:
- List releases: GH_PAGER="" gh release list --repo <owner/repo>
- View release: GH_PAGER="" gh release view <tag> --repo <owner/repo>
- Create release: GH_PAGER="" gh release create <tag> --repo <owner/repo>
- Upload asset: GH_PAGER="" gh release upload <tag> <files...> --repo <owner/repo> 